tags.description: Awutu Winton SHS is a non-profit (D.S.W./4562), private secondary education institution (No.GES/CR/ PSC/10/045) in Awutu Beraku, Central Region Ghana.

tags.description: A day school offering three courses. The school has a lot of professional and hardworking staff.

tags.description: The school was established in 1991. It was the “Brain Child” of the chiefs and people of Kwanyako. It had the backing and support of the government at the time. The school started in the Catholic Basic School classroom block nicknamed “the castle”.
tags.name: Kwanyako Senior High School

tags.description: Nsaba Presbyterian Senior High School started as Teacher Training College in 1962, with the The first batch of students were thirty–five (35), and made up of boys only. It has a very conducive environment that enhances good academic work.
tags.name: Nsaba Presbyterian Senior High School

tags.description: Obrachire Senior High Technical School is coeducational institution established in January 1991 as part of government policy to bring education to the doorstep of every Ghanaian child.
tags.name: Obrachire Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: Odupong SHS is an E-block school established in 2016. It is located in Odupong-Kasoa along the Jei- River farms. It is a mixed school.
tags.name: Odupong Community Senior High School

tags.description: Ogyeedom Community Senior High Technical is a newly absorbed school in Gomoa Afransi located right at the entrance into Afransi township opposite the District Education office.
tags.name: Ogyeedom Community Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: The school was established by the Ahmadiyya Mission in 1972 under the Nusrat Jahan (Service to Humanity) Scheme introduced in Ghana by the then Worldwide Spiritual Leader, Hazrat Mirza Nasir Ahmad (Khalifatul Masih III) of the Ahmadiyya Muslim Community.
tags.name: Potsin T. I. Ahmadiyya Senior High School

tags.description: The school was founded by the late Joseph Essel in 1959 as a speed writing Secretariat. It was taken over by the Government in 1967 and moved to its present site in 1975 as Swedru School of Business.
tags.name: Swedru School of Business

tags.description: SWESCO is the first Ghana Educational Trust (GET) School established by the first President Osagyefo Dr Kwame Nkrumah in 1959. The school is located on the Swedru-Bawjiase highway in Swedru.
tags.name: Swedru Senior High School

tags.description: The school is situated in Adeiso a town 17 km from Nsawam on the Nsawam-Asamankese road.
tags.name: Adeiso Presbyterian Senior High School

tags.description: The school was established in the year 2016 as a community day school. The school derives its name from the fact that it is situated between two towns, Kwaobaah and Nyanoa, both of which are in the Upper West Akim District of the Eastern Region.
tags.name: Kwaobaah Nyanoa Community Senior High School

tags.description: Ngleshie Amanfro Senior High School, formerly known as Torkuse Secondary School is situated in the Ga South Municipality.
tags.name: Ngleshie Amanfro Senior High School

tags.description: The school is located off the Koforidua central part of Asamankese on the Asamankese-Nsawam road. It is a Catholic co-educational institution.
tags.name: St. Thomas Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: It is a government institution established in February 2013 by the United National High Commission for refugees (UNHCR) to the Gomoa Fetteh Traditional Council for releasing a piece of land for the settlement of refugees from Liberia during the civil war.
tags.name: Fettehman Senior High School

tags.description: MICS is a co-educational primary to secondary boarding school that opened its doors in August 2013 to students from all corners of the globe. MICS aspires to be a globally renowned centre for innovative international education.
